        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 5:15PM PDT by NWS Portland OR</headline>
        <description>At 514 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles northeast of Breitenbush Springs, or 21 miles northeast of
Detroit, moving northwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Detroit, Idanha, Bagby Hot Springs, Timothy Lake, Three Lynx,
Breitenbush Springs, and Table Rock.

In Oregon this includes State Highway 22 east of Salem between mile
markers 52 and 60.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building or vehicle.

Reports of brief heavy rain and half inch in diameter hail has been
reported earlier with these storms.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
